>On another note, I've been trying to figure out if this scenario
>would work: run your message through RSA or whatever your choice
>is, then send it through a Clipper chip.  Seems to me that there
>shouldn't be any way to tell by the final encrypted message that
>this was done, unless an attempt is made to eavesdrop.  
>
>If the government then cracks down on you, wouldn't it be
>conceivable to sue for illegal wiretapping?  Unless of course
>they had a reason...in any case, they wouldn't know what you're
>saying.  
>
>I realize this is more complicated than it should be, and I don't
>profess to be an expert on cryptography, but it seems like a work-
>around that makes you look like a typical PC citizen, without
>surrendering your privacy to the public good.
>
